  "bio": [
    "Sergio Stevanato is chairman of the board emeritus of the Stevanato Group, a medical packaging firm based in Piombino Dese, Italy.",
    "Founded by his father Giovanni in 1949, the company is now run by his sons Franco and Marco, who serve as chairman and vice chairman, respectively.",
    "Stevanato Group went public on the New York Stock Exchange in July 2021.",
    "Stevanato Group is the second-largest maker of glass vials in the world and a major supplier of vials for several Covid-19 vaccine manufacturers.",
    "The company started out making glass bottles for wine and perfume and is now the world's largest producer of insulin pen cartridges."
  ],
  "about": [
    "He owns a winery in northeast Italy, Tenuta Stella, named after the Stevanato Group's original name, Soffieria Stella.",
    "In 2007 he was appointed a Cavaliere del Lavoro, one of Italy's highest civilian honors."
  ]
